"ngram\": \"2.10m.\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2229}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to Tebogo, the USA's Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone was rewarded in the track category for breaking her own world record in the women's 400m hurdles, clocking 50.37 to win gold in Paris, while men's Olympic marathon champion Tamirat Tola of Ethiopia picked up the out-of-stadium prize.\", \"from\": 2231, \"to\": 2523, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2258, \"end\": 2261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9856889608165735, \"rank\": 0.014516912354198082, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2264, \"end\": 2270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999970213547181, \"rank\": 1.8646604191008984e-06, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}, {\"begin\": 2418, \"end\": 2423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999786269, \"rank\": 2.1217844637469264e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2463, \"end\": 2475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tamirat_Tola\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tamirat Tola\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tamirat_Tola\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tamirat_Tola\"}, {\"begin\": 2479, \"end\": 2487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.418182175848939e-13, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 2234, \"to\": 224